00:27:09.850 --> 00:27:14.340
One must supply these from
imagination and do so impromptu."

00:27:14.340 --> 00:27:16.360
End of quote.

00:27:16.360 --> 00:27:18.630
What makes Arabic and its
users so radically different

00:27:18.630 --> 00:27:22.000
from the languages of Europe
and their users, Vulni suggests,

00:27:22.000 --> 00:27:26.820
is incomplete and even perverted
binding of letter of written sign,

00:27:26.820 --> 00:27:31.770
grapheme, to sound phoning to
image and ultimately also to sense.

00:27:31.770 --> 00:27:35.710 position:56%
Arabic writing, so goes the
charge, does not depict spoken words

00:27:35.710 --> 00:27:38.140
or does not paint them with
sufficient faithfulness

00:27:38.140 --> 00:27:40.920
to the sounds they
ostensibly must recall

00:27:40.920 --> 00:27:44.680
or to the images they
ostensibly must conjure forth.

00:27:44.680 --> 00:27:48.550
In such a system, enunciation
is not simply a question

00:27:48.550 --> 00:27:51.930
of [foreign language],
taking the floor, you know,

00:27:51.930 --> 00:27:57.990
launching the spoken word,
it is rather a question

00:27:57.990 --> 00:28:02.080
of [foreign language], painting
or depicting the spoken word.

00:28:02.080 --> 00:28:06.210
And to the extent that the writer
of Arabic writes only half words,

00:28:06.210 --> 00:28:10.990
he or she eats them, no longer able
in Vulni's judgment to communicate

00:28:10.990 --> 00:28:14.780
and thereby to enter the sphere
